Reasoning: The paper discusses a new dataset for reading comprehension problems, which involves constructing questions based on two independent articles. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it covers NLP and text processing. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories as they cover machine learning and AI techniques used in NLP. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as it covers techniques for retrieving relevant information from large datasets. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still relevant as it covers neural network models used in NLP tasks.
